title: ‘A constant fear’: Myanmar nationals face imprisonment back home as US ends protected status
summary: Thousands of Myanmar nationals living in the U.S. face potential deportation following the government's decision to end their Temporary Protected Status (TPS). The move affects expatriates who fled violence and instability in Myanmar. Advocates are raising concerns about the safety and logistical challenges of returning to a troubled homeland.

title: Millions in China cram for civil service exam and the hope of a job for life
summary: In light of challenging economic conditions, many individuals in China are increasingly favoring careers in the public sector. This shift represents a search for stability amid uncertainty. The trend highlights a growing preference for secure employment opportunities in government roles.

title: Palestinian Australian assaulted and abused on Sydney train ‘shocked’ police charged assailant with assault but not hate speech
summary: A video has surfaced showing the assault on Shamikh Badra, which has drawn condemnation from the attorney general, who deemed the incident "unacceptable."
